Subject: New SPO event type needs mapping
Description:
Customer is receiving a couple warnings in SPAC System Scan related to the following unknown event type (job logs attached):
SiteSensitivityLabelApplied
What_We_Know__c:
Unknown Event Type: SiteSensitivityLabelApplied

Hotfix auditor-enterprise-hotfix-11.6.0.069.zip was deployed post-upgrade to NEA v11.6.0.138. SPAC is scheduled for daily run.
Next_Steps__c: Once we have confirmation of a successful SPAC run with no more warnings related to the SiteSensitivityLabelApplied, we can close this ticket out.
Solution_Comment__c: SiteSensitiveLabelApplied was added to the NAA product in 11.6.0.139. HF 11.6.0.69 was deployed to add this in the customer's .138 environment.
